dsDescriptionValue.value:
Three of the FITS files contain position-position-velocity (PPV) data cubes of the Orion BN/KL outflow. The data were taken in late 2012 and early 2013 with the Apache Point Observatory's near-IR TripleSpec spectrograph. Due to large file size, the three spectral bands (J, H, and K) are contained in separate FITS files. This data is presented in Youngblood, Ginsburg, & Bally (2016).

Other files included are data products made from the PPV cubes used in Youngblood, Ginsburg, & Bally (2016) and may be accessed upon request.

files.description:
Visual extinction determined from the flux ratio of the H2 1-0 Q(3) and 1-0 S(1) lines.
This is a FITS file with 1 (primary) HDU.
The following recognized metadata keys have been found in the FITS file:
CRVAL2; NAXIS; NAXIS1; NAXIS0; CRVAL1;
